An Interlake man has been hospitalized after contracting the measles virus. Manitoba health officials confirm the man in his 40s resides in the area of the Interlake-Eastern Regional Health Authority.

The man infected attended the following locations and events while contagious:
- 7 and 8 Mar 2014: Manitoba Winter Games badminton tournament in Winkler,
- 8 Mar 2014: 204 Volleyball and Ice Time Sports 14 and under tournament, at Monroe and John Henderson junior high schools in Winnipeg
- 9 Mar 2014: University of Manitoba Bison volleyball tournament in Winnipeg
- 9 Mar 2014, between 11 am and 4 pm: Victoria Hospital emergency department in Winnipeg
- 10 Mar 2014 at 7:00 pm: Selkirk General Hospital emergency department in Selkirk

People who attended these events or locations, who think they might have measles or have been in close contact with someone who has been diagnosed with measles, should phone their health-care provider or phone Health Links-Info Sant√© at (204) 788-8200 or 1-888-315-9257 for more information.

