******
[15] New Zealand (Auckland)
Date: Tue 11 Mar 2014
Source: 3 News [edited]
http://www.3news.co.nz/New-measles-outbreak-warning/tabid/423/articleID/335445/Default.aspx


Passengers on 2 domestic flights and another from Singapore to Auckland may have caught measles after 2 people infected with the illness travelled earlier this month [March 2014].

A person, who was not a confirmed case at the time, flew from Auckland to Christchurch on [2 Mar 2014] and made a return trip 2 days later. Both were Air New Zealand flights -- NZ501 and NZ548.
Another infectious passenger travelled from Singapore to Auckland on Singapore Airlines flight SQ285 on [4 Mar 2014].

Auckland Regional Public Health Service's medical officer of health Dr Richard Hoskins says it can take 10-14 days for someone who has caught measles to start showing any symptoms.
He says anyone on these flights who may have caught measles should be starting to feel unwell, if they're not already, up to [18 Mar 2014].

Passengers who sat nearest the infected passengers will be contacted by their local public health service as they have the highest risk, Dr Hoskins says. Anyone who was feeling unwell should call their GP.

There have been 69 confirmed cases in Auckland this year [2014] with 46 of the cases linked to Westland Boys' High School.

